{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":140096,"duration_api_ms":153099,"num_turns":19,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"f33522c2-8fe5-4474-9958-8deeaf83dc4a","total_cost_usd":0.8250198,"usage":{"input_tokens":18,"cache_creation_input_tokens":52834,"cache_read_input_tokens":654123,"output_tokens":3366,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":52834,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":18,"outputTokens":3366,"cacheReadInputTokens":654123,"cacheCreationInputTokens":52834,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.741514,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000},"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001":{"inputTokens":26,"outputTokens":7914,"cacheReadInputTokens":66373,"cacheCreationInputTokens":29818,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.08350579999999999,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"amendments":[{"body":"The `debug_assert!` in `unique_terminal_replay_match` (fs.rs:2824) only fires in debug builds. In release builds, calling `(Some(run_id), None)` silently bypasses the started_at guard on runless terminal candidates, allowing backfill onto the wrong legacy row. Replace `debug_assert!` with a runtime check that returns `None` (or panics) to enforce the contract in all build modes.","rationale":"The doc comment on `unique_terminal_replay_match` explicitly states 'When requested_run_id is Some, requested_started_at must also be Some' — this is a safety invariant, not a performance assertion. In release builds the debug_assert is stripped, so a future caller violating this contract would silently skip the started_at guard and potentially backfill the wrong terminal row. All current call sites happen to pass correct arguments, but the function is internal and could be called from new code paths. A runtime enforcement (e.g., return None early) costs nothing and prevents a subtle data-integrity regression."},{"body":"The plan_hash auto-population from snapshot in `record_task_run_start` (fs.rs:3017-3019) runs unconditionally for new entries, but the comment block at fs.rs:2988-2992 explains that snapshot-based backfill is intentionally NOT applied to existing rows because persist_plan() can advance the snapshot hash after the original attempt started. However, the same race applies to new entries: if a plan is persisted between the bead being dispatched and `record_task_run_start` being called, the new entry gets stamped with the newer plan hash even though the bead was dispatched under the older plan. Consider documenting this known limitation in the code comment, or having the caller always supply plan_hash explicitly when it knows which plan version dispatched the bead.","rationale":"The implementation correctly avoids mislabeling existing rows (the tests `legacy_open_row_without_plan_hash_not_mislabeled_after_plan_evolution` and `start_replay_after_plan_evolution_does_not_conflict` verify this). But for brand-new entries, `snapshot_plan_hash()` reads the current snapshot, which may have advanced since dispatch. The window is small but real, and the existing comments only discuss the existing-row case. A documentation note acknowledging this edge case would prevent future confusion about whether the auto-population is truly race-free."}],"summary":"The implementation correctly addresses all three issues from the project prompt. Issue 1 (struct drift): The duplicate `StartJournalDetails` and `CompletionJournalDetails` structs in fs.rs are eliminated — both now import the canonical structs from model.rs, which use `deny_unknown_fields` for compile-time safety. The `json_fill_none` generic merge replaces manual per-field merging, making future field additions automatically included. Issue 2 (runless-to-named completion): The `update_task_run` path now accepts a runless match when `started_at` matches, and correctly rejects with an informative error when it doesn't. The `unique_terminal_replay_match` function adds a parallel started_at guard for terminal replay. Issue 3 (plan_hash auto-population): New entry creation in `record_task_run_start` auto-populates plan_hash from the milestone snapshot, while existing rows are deliberately not stamped (to avoid mislabeling after plan evolution). The service layer correctly delegates auto-population to the FS adapter rather than duplicating the logic. All 683 tests pass, including 6 new targeted regression tests. Two minor issues found: the `debug_assert!` contract enforcement and a documentation gap on the new-entry auto-population race window."},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"2e99363d-5afb-41dc-bcb7-c7fee41a6fa5"}
